{"id":"979","name":"happy-hour-runaway-train","title":"Happy Hour: Runaway Train","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2008-09-17T18:16:00-05:00","tags":["adam dread","alexander radulov","belmont","davidson county","gas shortage","hockey","khl","myspace","nashville predators","neely&apos;s bend middle school","nhl","predators","preds","presidential debate","russia","tennessean","town hall debate","twitter"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you are new here, you might want to <a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to the RSS feed</strong></a> for updates on this topic.<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/ytwhitelight/232435604/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm1.static.flickr.com/98/232435604_319539647f.jpg?v=0\" alt=\"\"></a></p><ul><li>The Preds are going to the mattresses to get things settled with forward Alexander Radulov, who decided he didn&#x2019;t feel like coming back stateside and decided that hockey in Russia is cooler. [<a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=9027574\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WTVF</a>]</li><li>Former Metro Councilman/stand-up comedian/wave-maker extraordinaire Adam Dread is back in the spotlight these days stirring up some drama with the <em>Tennessean</em>. Just when we thought things were getting boring around here&#x2026; [<a href=\"http://blogs.nashvillescene.com/pitw/2008/09/adam_dread_fires_back_at_tenne.php\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;blogs.nashvillescene.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Pith In The Wind</a>]</li><li>Hey, have you heard Belmont&#x2019;s <a href=\"http://www.belmontdebate08.com/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.belmontdebate08.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">hosting a presidential debate</a>? Oh, also, you can now submit your questions for the candidates through <a href=\"http://www.mydebates.org\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.mydebates.org&apos;]);\">MyDebates.org</a> in partnership with Myspace. And there will be <a href=\"http://politics.nashvillepost.com/2008/09/17/the-debates-will-be-twitterized/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;politics.nashvillepost.com&apos;]);\">live Twittering</a>. Oi. [<a href=\"http://tnelection.blogspot.com/2008/09/submit-debate-question-at-new-myspace.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;tnelection.blogspot.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Tennessean Election Blog</a>]</li><li>Neely&#x2019;s Bend Middle School in Madison (yep, still Davidson County) confirmed a case of the highly contagious and nasty MRSA. [<a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=9027809\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WKRN</a>]</li><li>You&#x2019;ve probably noticed your regular fill-up stations running out of gas in the past few days; it could be a while before they get fuel again. [<a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=9027972\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WKRN</a>]</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://flickr.com/photos/ytwhitelight/232435604/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">ytwhitelight</a>.</em></p><p>No related posts.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}